I noticed that several people in the US have commented that they were unable to play this because it is Region 2.  I am a fan of Brit flicks and I used to be frustrated that a number of DVDs I wanted were only available in Region 2.  Then a couple of years ago it occurred to me to check on what a Region 2 DVD player would cost.  I discovered that all region DVD players were available here on Amazon starting under $30.  I immediately ordered the least expensive one and have been very happy with it.  Since it plays any region, I just use it for all my DVDs.  If you are a connoisseur of high quality electronics, you would probably prefer to shell out more for a better one.  I am not, so this one suits my needs just fine.  Since that time I have been able to order a number of my British favorites, both here and from Amazon UK.  All in all, I am a very happy anglophile.
